text: Started crying watching this trailer. As an adult sufferer of Tourettes, I have spent many years being ostracized, bullied, dismissed, and misunderstood. Up til now my media representation has been as the butt of a joke at best. I am so tired of hearing South Park and What About Bob references, and those tools were used to belittle and marginalize me growing up. Seeing this means the world to me. Seeing this means the world to future kids like me. Knowing that maybe the conversation surrounding this condition can change is so amazing. Christ, hearing a major actor with the same tics as me... god, that means everything. I will be seeing this movie. I hope you will, too.

text: For anyone who wants to know: His character has Tourette‚Äôs Syndrome. It is a neurological condition where the brain sends false or inappropriate signals to to the body. It means uncontrollable tics. I won‚Äôt say I know them all since I don‚Äôt. Everyone with Tourette‚Äôs is different and have different triggers. Mainly triggers come from nervous, anxious, excited, and any emotion except calmness. Talking about it to a person with it can sometimes trigger them. -Please no hate or saying I‚Äôm wrong because like I said it is different for everyone! I‚Äôm just going off on my personal experience with it and I love educating people over it! If anyone has questions feel free to ask!

text: Man, am I think only one who thinks this movie looks insanely cheap? It's like they blew their entire $26 million budget on the admittedly impressive cast. The lighting and cinematography are incredibly flat and boring (a terrible idea in a noir film of all things!), many of the sets and locations don't look convincingly period (especially the streets with their obviously-modern street signs and traffic lights), and even some of the costumes are lacking. I own an identical Carhartt jacket to the one Norton wears, right down to the color. I think I bought it in 2012. I don't think that particular style of jacket has changed much over the years, but couldn't they at least have weathered it a bit? Mine is significantly more worn-looking. text: i thought this  was a good movie. As Rotten Tomatoes notes it is a little too long. But it does reward the viewers. At least there is attempt to make a good film.The probably ought have to edited it by a good 20-30 minutes. They also could not build up the suspense as well as they could have. In the end it seemed a bit too easy. maybe slight changes in screenplay were required. keep certain plot points hidden from the viewer till the end. So maybe reduced runtime and more suspenseful annd mysterious build up could have made this a far better film. Edward Norton was great and the rest of  the cast was good though Willis could have done better in the opening scenes. The most interesting idea was to relate Baldwin and Dafeo. A B from me. At some point the actors and cast and crew of Motherless Brooklyn would look back at the film with satisfaction.  I think with time this movie will get better.
